## 📊 Log Analysis Patterns

### 1. Efficient Log Filtering
```bash
# Save full execution log once
pnpm playground:generate 2>&1 | tee logs/full-execution.log

# Filter specific patterns without re-execution
grep -A5 -B5 "RULE-9-DEBUG" logs/full-execution.log
grep -A10 -B10 "assistant.message_complete" logs/full-execution.log
grep "Round.*2.*thinking" logs/full-execution.log
```

### 2. Log Analysis Commands
```bash
# Create analysis shortcuts
alias log-rule9="grep -A5 -B5 'RULE-9-DEBUG' logs/full-execution.log"
alias log-assistant="grep -A10 -B10 'assistant.message_complete' logs/full-execution.log"
alias log-round2="grep 'Round.*2' logs/full-execution.log"
alias log-execution="grep -A20 -B10 'ExecutionService' logs/full-execution.log"
```

### 3. Cached Log Analysis
- Save logs to `logs/` directory with timestamps
- Use file-based filtering instead of re-running examples
- Create analysis scripts for common debugging patterns
- Cache validation results alongside execution logs

